  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "GWB Assistant Relationship Manager - (GRIT)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Assignment:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>As an Assistant Relationship Manager (ARM)  in GFIG, you will gain exposure to the dynamic world of institutional banking and contribute meaningfully to the team’s strategic and operational initiatives.</p>\n<p>• Client &amp; Credit Engagement: Support Relationship Managers and Credit Analysts in client servicing, credit analysis, and internal liaison activities.</p>\n<p>• Market Research &amp; Analysis: Conduct market research and competitor benchmarking to support strategic initiatives and client pitches.</p>\n<p>• Productivity Initiatives: Working on projects to streamline workflows and improve team productivity through automation, data analytics, digital tools, and process enhancements</p>\n<p>• Projects Support: Participate in special projects, offering cross-functional exposure and learning opportunities, for example, system testing, AI prompt development/ testing, process improvement, dashboard design.</p>\n<p>• Business Support: Assist in day-to-day business administration including reporting, marketing coordination, banking processes, and internal project tracking.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Outcomes:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>• Hands-on experience in institutional banking and financial markets.</p>\n<p>• Exposure to client relationship management and credit processes.</p>\n<p>• Opportunity to work with senior bankers and cross-functional teams.</p>\n<p>• Development of analytical, communication, and project management skills.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>This is 6 months traineeship under Graduate Industry Traineeship (GRIT) programme.</p>",
